								"description": "Creates a new fx_currency2_instance record in ServiceNow. Use the returned sys_id to reference this currency instance in unit_price or total_line_amount fields on related records.\n\nEndpoint\n- Method: POST\n- URL: https://illumindev.service-now.com/api/now/table/fx_currency2_instance\n\nHeaders\n- Accept: application/json\n- Content-Type: application/json\n\nAuth\n- This instance typically requires authentication. Ensure valid credentials or an API key are configured in your active environment (e.g., via variables {{username}} / {{password}} or instance-specific auth).\n\nPath/Query Params\n- None.\n\nRequest Body (raw JSON)\n{\n  \"fx_currency\": \"{{currencyCode}}\",   // ISO 4217 currency code (e.g., USD, EUR)\n  \"value\": \"{{amount}}\"                // Numeric amount as string; decimals allowed\n}\n\nVariables\n- {{currencyCode}}: ISO 4217 currency code for the instance you want to create.\n- {{amount}}: The monetary value for this instance.\n\nSample Use\n- Set currencyCode=USD and amount=1234.56 in your environment, then send the request.\n\nExpected Response\n- 201 Created with a body containing the new record, including the field sys_id.\n\nPost-creation\n- Use the returned sys_id in related records (e.g., Purchase Order Line) for unit_price or total_line_amount.\n\nCommon Errors\n- 400 Bad Request: Missing or invalid fields.\n- 401/403 Unauthorized: Verify authentication or permissions.\n\nNotes\n- This request does not currently include pre-request or test scripts. Consider adding tests to assert status code === 201 and that a sys_id is present in the response."
